Notices.NoticeContent: You are not eligible to register until you check in with International Student Services, UW-Bothell, Husky Hall 1212.
Your estimated Period I Priority Registration Date for winter quarter is . Registration begins at 6:00 a.m.

Before You Register
Beginning one week prior to each quarter's registration period you can take care of all the required Notices and Insurance/Optional Charges selections so that when your priority registratrion period begins, you can go directly into Web Registration. If you have not already done so, go to the Insurance/Optional Charges services now to take care of these requirements prior to registering for summer quarter.

Before You Register MK II
Beginning one week prior to each quarter's registration period you can take care of all the required Notices and Insurance/Optional Charges selections so that when your priority registratrion period begins, you can go directly into Web Registration. If you have not already done so, go to the Insurance/Optional Charges services now to take care of these requirements prior to registering for summer quarter.

Online ISS information session required before registration
All new international students are required to complete the International Student Services(ISS) Online Information Session before registering for classes. You will need your UW NetID and password to access the online ISS information session. After you arrive on campus the International Student Services(ISS) must collect copies of your immigration documents.

The following offices have placed administrative holds on your academic record which will prevent further registration and/or ordering official transcripts:

Type: Registration/Transcript Office: Student Fiscal Services, 129 Schmitz, 206-543-4694
